for a bloody horse.

17
00:01:56.240 --> 00:01:58.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Of course we're not swapping it.

18
00:01:59.200 --> 00:02:02.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
- That would be mad.
- We're going to play two-up.

19
00:02:21.960 --> 00:02:24.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Here you are.
- I knew it.

20
00:02:24.360 --> 00:02:26.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I knew it.
Tommy, you bloody idiot.

21
00:02:26.880 --> 00:02:28.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Shut up, Arthur, I won.

22
00:02:28.760 --> 00:02:30.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Good.
- I promised Johnny,

23
00:02:30.480 --> 00:02:33.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'd let him have a spin
in the car if he lost.

24
00:02:33.240 --> 00:02:34.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
All right.

25
00:02:34.520 --> 00:02:36.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[laughing]

26
00:02:39.280 --> 00:02:41.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Are you Lee boys
laughing at my brother?

27
00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:45.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you?

28
00:02:46.120 --> 00:02:49.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Eh? I asked you a question.
- Tommy, come on!

29
00:02:49.720 --> 00:02:51.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Come on, it's just a crack.

30
00:02:51.480 --> 00:02:54.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Get your family out of here
and go and enjoy yourselves

31
00:02:54.760 --> 00:02:56.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
at the fair
before they start a war.

32
00:02:56.920 --> 00:03:02.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Go on. Go. They're from good people.
Their granddad was a King.

33
00:03:02.520 --> 00:03:04.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Their granddad was a King.

34
00:03:04.840 --> 00:03:07.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yeah, but his mother
was a Diddicoy whore.

35
00:04:34.120 --> 00:04:37.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We will take them
before last night's beer,

36
00:04:37.360 --> 00:04:40.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
turns to piss and wakes the devils up.

37
00:04:40.680 --> 00:04:42.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We will leave no stone unturned.

38
00:04:43.000 --> 00:04:47.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Every gun, every bullet
will be brought to me for inspection.

39
00:04:47.280 --> 00:04:50.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now, take your positions.

40
00:05:11.680 --> 00:05:14.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[whistle blowing]

41
00:05:15.360 --> 00:05:17.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[people screaming]

42
00:05:23.640 --> 00:05:25.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[breathing heavily]

43
00:05:27.560 --> 00:05:28.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Freddie.

44
00:05:30.560 --> 00:05:32.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[knock at door]

45
00:05:32.120 --> 00:05:33.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[panting]

46
00:05:33.600 --> 00:05:36.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're sure your brothers are at the fair?

47
00:05:36.160 --> 00:05:38.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If it was them, they wouldn't knock.

48
00:05:38.440 --> 00:05:39.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man] Mr. Thorne!

49
00:05:40.440 --> 00:05:41.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What is it?

50
00:05:41.600 --> 00:05:44.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The police are rounding up the communists.

51
00:05:44.800 --> 00:05:48.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Come on, Ada, if the cops
find me we are screwed. Fuck!

52
00:05:50.040 --> 00:05:52.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- [policeman] Freddie Thorne, open up!
- Ada!

53
00:06:01.360 --> 00:06:04.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[screaming]

54
00:06:11.360 --> 00:06:14.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You have to jump, Ada.
I'll catch you. Come on.

55
00:06:22.640 --> 00:06:24.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Look at this.

56
00:06:24.360 --> 00:06:28.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
A prescription for iron tablets
for Ada fucking Shelby.

57
00:06:30.080 --> 00:06:31.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[knocking on door]

58
00:06:31.400 --> 00:06:33.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mrs. Donovan, I need that favor.

59
00:06:33.400 --> 00:06:36.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Come in and be quick.
- I'm not coming in. She is.

60
00:06:36.520 --> 00:06:38.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Holy Jesus, it's the Shelby girl.

61
00:06:38.600 --> 00:06:40.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You've not seen her with me, okay?

62
00:06:40.680 --> 00:06:42.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Just give her a cup of tea and let her
stay until the police have gone.

63
00:06:42.760 --> 00:06:45.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
She's the sister of those
Peaky Blinder devils.

64
00:06:45.840 --> 00:06:48.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And yet, she is an angel.
Come on, Ada.

65
00:06:48.760 --> 00:06:50.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are you going to do, Freddie?

66
00:06:50.880 --> 00:06:53.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Me? I'm gonna have to
leave town for a bit.

67
00:06:56.000 --> 00:06:58.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[women shouting]

68
00:07:04.200 --> 00:07:06.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[door opens]

69
00:07:10.760 --> 00:07:13.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A gentleman would take off his hat,

70
00:07:14.560 --> 00:07:16.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and put out his pipe.

71
00:07:24.640 --> 00:07:26.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I see you Specials
only dare come here,

72
00:07:27.000 --> 00:07:29.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
when you know the boys
are away at the fair.

73
00:07:29.680 --> 00:07:31.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You mean your nephews?

74
00:07:31.720 --> 00:07:36.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
With their guns and their razors?
Is it them you're lighting candles for?

75
00:07:37.280 --> 00:07:38.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No.

76
00:07:38.400 --> 00:07:41.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I am lighting candles
for the boys from the Garrison

77
00:07:41.560 --> 00:07:43.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
who lost their lives in France.

78
00:07:44.760 --> 00:07:46.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's a list there.

79
00:07:48.200 --> 00:07:49.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Look.

80
00:07:54.520 --> 00:07:58.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I hear you didn't make it to France,
Inspector Campbell.

81
00:08:01.840 --> 00:08:03.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You've heard of me.

82
00:08:04.880 --> 00:08:06.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've heard of you.

83
00:08:09.840 --> 00:08:12.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Is it the Holy Grail you're looking for?

84
00:08:12.440 --> 00:08:17.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
As a matter of fact,
it is the Holy Grail I'm looking for.

85
00:08:17.280 --> 00:08:20.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Something precious.
Something stolen.

86
00:08:20.680 --> 00:08:23.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Perhaps you know
what I'm talking about.

87
00:08:25.960 --> 00:08:30.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Sorry, I misunderstood your intention
when you pushed me against the wall.

88
00:08:42.760 --> 00:08:45.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Turn the place upside down.

89
00:08:47.840 --> 00:08:50.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Arthur Shelby said you people
would help us.

90
00:08:50.440 --> 00:08:53.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If we don't know what you've lost,
how can we help you find it?

91
00:08:53.800 --> 00:08:56.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But I have found out subsequently that
I was speaking to the wrong man.

92
00:08:56.400 --> 00:08:59.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Next time I want to talk to the boss.

93
00:09:00.760 --> 00:09:04.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Lickey Tea Rooms. Friday, ten o'clock

94
00:09:04.480 --> 00:09:07.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And when I say, "The boss,"
I mean Thomas.

95
00:09:12.640 --> 00:09:13.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Come on.

96
00:09:39.800 --> 00:09:42.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Now, what the bloody hell's
been going on here?

97
00:09:44.600 --> 00:09:45.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jesus Christ.

98
00:09:45.720 --> 00:09:47.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Polly]<i> The coppers told everyone</i>

99
00:09:47.840 --> 00:09:50.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Arthur'd agreed to it</i>
<i>when he was arrested.</i>

100
00:09:50.400 --> 00:09:54.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They said the Peaky Blinders had cleared
out to the fair to let them do it.

101
00:09:54.840 --> 00:09:58.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I never said nothing to that copper about
smashing up bloody houses.

102
00:09:58.920 --> 00:10:03.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- All right. Which pubs did they do?
- The Guns, the Chain, the Marquis.

103
00:10:03.200 --> 00:10:05.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
All the ones that pay you
to protect them.

104
00:10:05.760 --> 00:10:08.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Only one they didn't touch
was the Garrison.

105
00:10:08.440 --> 00:10:11.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Make sure people think
we were in on it.

106
00:10:11.440 --> 00:10:13.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's smart, this copper.

107
00:10:14.520 --> 00:10:16.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So, go on.
Drink your beers, get out.

108
00:10:16.760 --> 00:10:20.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You'd better show people you are still
the cocks of the walk.

109
00:10:20.400 --> 00:10:23.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Hand out some cash
to the landlords of the pubs.

110
00:10:23.280 --> 00:10:25.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Pay some veterans
to fix the places up.

111
00:10:25.600 --> 00:10:29.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- [John] Nipper, give us the bag.
- So, what about you, Tommy?

112
00:10:29.280 --> 00:10:32.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I have to go to Charlie's
to stable the horse.

113
00:10:32.080 --> 00:10:34.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She looked footsore in the box.

114
00:10:37.400 --> 00:10:39.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let them see your faces.

115
00:10:47.720 --> 00:10:50.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So we both know
what they were looking for.

116
00:10:55.840 --> 00:10:59.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- You don't read the papers.
- Racing papers.

117
00:10:59.560 --> 00:11:01.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So let me tell you the odds.

118
00:11:01.800 --> 00:11:04.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I reckon it's three to one,
there'll be a revolution.

119
00:11:05.040 --> 00:11:08.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- I wouldn't bet on that.
- That copper's betting on it.

120
00:11:08.760 --> 00:11:12.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He's not going to let it rest
till he gets those guns back.

121
00:11:17.640 --> 00:11:18.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighing]

122
00:11:19.640 --> 00:11:21.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Did he talk to you, Pol?

123
00:11:22.880 --> 00:11:24.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
In the church.

124
00:11:25.480 --> 00:11:27.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Did he try to find our Ada?

125
00:11:28.440 --> 00:11:29.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She was sleeping.

126
00:11:30.360 --> 00:11:31.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[scoffing]

127
00:11:33.280 --> 00:11:35.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Where was she sleeping, Pol?

128
00:11:36.760 --> 00:11:39.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I thought you didn't care
for women's business.

129
00:11:45.360 --> 00:11:48.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He knows you're the boss.
He wants to meet you.

130
00:11:55.280 --> 00:11:57.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Will you talk to him?
- No.

131
00:11:59.240 --> 00:12:01.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You don't parley
when you're on the back foot.

132
00:12:03.920 --> 00:12:06.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We'll strike a blow back first.

133
00:12:22.000 --> 00:12:24.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Finn, lad?
What are you doing?

134
00:12:24.480 --> 00:12:26.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're having a fire.

135
00:12:26.200 --> 00:12:27.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[knock on door]

136
00:12:27.960 --> 00:12:30.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Two bob for your picture of the King.
- What?

137
00:12:30.800 --> 00:12:32.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Bring it to Watery Lane.

138
00:12:32.760 --> 00:12:34.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Hello, Finn lad.
- Hello, Scud.

139
00:12:34.840 --> 00:12:37.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Scudboat] We are blocking
the entrance, mate.

140
00:12:39.000 --> 00:12:40.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Come on.

141
00:12:44.720 --> 00:12:45.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[people cheering]

142
00:12:54.440 --> 00:12:55.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Chuck them on, boys.

143
00:12:55.920 --> 00:12:57.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[all cheering]

144
00:13:01.160 --> 00:13:03.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I hope to God you know
what you're doing.

145
00:13:23.720 --> 00:13:27.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm a reporter
with the <i>Birmingham Evening Despatch.</i>

146
00:13:27.480 --> 00:13:29.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I had a phone call.

147
00:13:29.640 --> 00:13:32.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Someone called Thomas Shelby?

148
00:13:32.200 --> 00:13:33.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Come with me.

149
00:13:35.440 --> 00:13:38.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Fred] Come on, folks,
give us a bit of room.

150
00:13:38.120 --> 00:13:39.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Tommy.

151
00:13:39.840 --> 00:13:41.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Move back for us, please, folks.

152
00:13:41.880 --> 00:13:43.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- You're Mr. Shelby?
- I am.

153
00:13:43.600 --> 00:13:45.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
All the way back, please.

154
00:13:47.640 --> 00:13:51.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- You said, I would be protected.
- You're protected.

155
00:13:52.200 --> 00:13:53.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's going on?

156
00:13:53.880 --> 00:13:56.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There are some things
I want you to write down.

157
00:13:58.000 --> 00:13:59.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now, first of all,

158
00:13:59.640 --> 00:14:03.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
it's not that people around here
are disloyal to the King.

159
00:14:03.120 --> 00:14:04.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's the opposite.

160
00:14:04.320 --> 00:14:07.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You see, we don't want
our beloved King looking down

161
00:14:07.440 --> 00:14:10.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and seeing the things
that are being done to us.

162
00:14:10.320 --> 00:14:12.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So we are taking down
his pictures.

163
00:14:12.400 --> 00:14:14.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But why are you burning them?

164
00:14:14.600 --> 00:14:17.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We went through hell for our King.

165
00:14:17.480 --> 00:14:20.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Walked through the flames of war.
Write all this down.

166
00:14:20.960 --> 00:14:24.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And now we're being attacked
in our own homes.

167
00:14:24.280 --> 00:14:26.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
These new coppers over from Belfast,

168
00:14:26.520 --> 00:14:29.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
breaking into our homes and interfering
with our women.

169
00:14:29.800 --> 00:14:33.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We don't think our King would
want to see that happening.

170
00:14:33.240 --> 00:14:36.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So we're lighting fires
to raise the alarm.

171
00:14:36.320 --> 00:14:39.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
May I ask you, in what capacity
do you speak?

172
00:14:39.760 --> 00:14:41.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No capacity.

173
00:14:41.840 --> 00:14:46.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I am an ordinary man.
I won gallantry medals at the Somme.

174
00:14:46.800 --> 00:14:50.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I want you to write in your paper
what's going on here.

175
00:14:51.280 --> 00:14:52.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Go on, go.

176
00:14:52.840 --> 00:14:57.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
muttering

177
00:14:57.360 --> 00:15:01.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
muttering

178
00:15:01.200 --> 00:15:02.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[knock on door]

179
00:15:02.360 --> 00:15:03.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Come in.

180
00:15:03.520 --> 00:15:04.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[door opens]

181
00:15:06.840 --> 00:15:11.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There, there. There's a telephone call
for you, sir, on the London line.

182
00:15:11.680 --> 00:15:14.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There is?
It's almost midnight.

183
00:15:14.360 --> 00:15:17.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's Mr. Winston Churchill, sir.

184
00:15:24.080 --> 00:15:25.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[door closes]

185
00:15:29.840 --> 00:15:31.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Yes, sir?
- Inspector Campbell.

186
00:15:31.840 --> 00:15:34.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I hear there has been
a bonfire in your city.

187
00:15:34.560 --> 00:15:38.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There was a small fire reported
at around nine o' clock on Watery Lane.

188
00:15:38.760 --> 00:15:41.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Certainly nothing to</i>
<i>trouble you about, sir.</i>

189
00:15:41.400 --> 00:15:44.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But I'm afraid it has troubled me.

190
00:15:44.280 --> 00:15:47.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Half an hour ago,
I received a wire communication

191
00:15:47.680 --> 00:15:51.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
from the editor
of the <i>Birmingham Evening Despatch.</i>

192
00:15:51.680 --> 00:15:55.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>It seems one of his reporters</i>
<i>was invited to the fire,</i>

193
00:15:55.440 --> 00:15:59.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>and discovered that they were burning</i>
<i>pictures of the King.</i>

194
00:15:59.160 --> 00:16:00.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Of the King?

195
00:16:00.840 --> 00:16:05.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Any newspaper report which may cause
embarrassment to His Majesty,

196
00:16:05.320 --> 00:16:09.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
is always referred first and as a matter
of routine to the Home Office.

197
00:16:09.720 --> 00:16:13.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I will go down there immediately
and arrest those involved.

198
00:16:13.200 --> 00:16:16.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No, you most certainly
will not make arrests.

199
00:16:16.880 --> 00:16:19.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>If there are arrests</i>
<i>there will be trials,</i>

200
00:16:19.360 --> 00:16:22.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>if there are trials there will be more</i>
<i>newspaper reports,</i>

201
00:16:22.880 --> 00:16:27.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
which will necessarily mention the burning
of the King's likeness.

202
00:16:27.640 --> 00:16:32.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I put you in Birmingham
for one very specific reason.

203
00:16:32.320 --> 00:16:35.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Are you any nearer to finding
those stolen guns?

204
00:16:36.040 --> 00:16:39.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- We are making steady progress.
- We need results.

205
00:16:39.120 --> 00:16:42.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Good night, Mr. Campbell.
<i>- Sir. Could I at least ask,</i>

206
00:16:42.920 --> 00:16:46.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
does this report name
any of those involved?

207
00:16:46.800 --> 00:16:52.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It names a Mr. Thomas Shelby.
The report mentions he is a war hero.

208
00:17:02.880 --> 00:17:04.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Good of you to join us.

209
00:17:05.200 --> 00:17:07.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Where have you been all day?
- [Ada] In bed.

210
00:17:08.360 --> 00:17:12.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Couldn't sleep.
Then I couldn't wake up.

211
00:17:12.120 --> 00:17:15.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Then I was cold and then I had
to go for a wee.

212
00:17:15.600 --> 00:17:20.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Then I was with this bear on a boat,
but that was just a dream.

213
00:17:20.320 --> 00:17:21.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Then I was hungry.

214
00:17:22.880 --> 00:17:24.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why are you reading the paper?

215
00:17:25.840 --> 00:17:26.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why wouldn't I be?

216
00:17:27.000 --> 00:17:29.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've never seen you
read the paper.

217
00:17:29.120 --> 00:17:31.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've only ever seen you
light fires with them.

218
00:17:31.840 --> 00:17:35.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
BSA are on strike.
The miners are on strike.

219
00:17:35.520 --> 00:17:39.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
IRA are killing our boys,
ten a day.

220
00:17:42.680 --> 00:17:43.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What?

221
00:17:44.600 --> 00:17:46.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Stand up.

222
00:17:46.160 --> 00:17:48.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Why?
- Just stand up.

223
00:17:54.920 --> 00:17:56.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Side on.

224
00:17:58.120 --> 00:17:59.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are you doing?

225
00:18:00.240 --> 00:18:01.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ada,

226
00:18:03.160 --> 00:18:04.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
how late are you?

227
00:18:07.440 --> 00:18:08.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
One week.

228
00:18:11.120 --> 00:18:12.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Five weeks.

229
00:18:13.160 --> 00:18:16.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Seven if you count weekends.
I think it's a lack of iron.

230
00:18:17.240 --> 00:18:18.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I got some tablets.

231
00:18:19.520 --> 00:18:20.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But they didn't work.

232
00:18:24.360 --> 00:18:25.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No.

233
00:18:34.960 --> 00:18:37.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Mrs. Simeon] You can
get dressed now, love.

234
00:18:38.120 --> 00:18:39.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, am I or not?

235
00:18:45.120 --> 00:18:48.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Keep bloody walking, Ada.
If anybody sees us here they'll know.

236
00:18:48.880 --> 00:18:51.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not getting rid of it, Aunt Pol.

237
00:18:51.120 --> 00:18:53.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Just come home
and we'll talk about it.

238
00:18:53.440 --> 00:18:55.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You get off me or I'll scream it.
I swear.

239
00:18:58.760 --> 00:19:02.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
All right, you want to do this
on the street, let's do it.

240
00:19:02.200 --> 00:19:03.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Whose is it?

241
00:19:03.520 --> 00:19:07.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If I tell you, you'll tell them
and they'll cut him to pieces.

242
00:19:07.520 --> 00:19:09.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not if he marries you, they won't.

243
00:19:12.160 --> 00:19:13.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Will he marry you?

244
00:19:14.080 --> 00:19:17.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- I don't know where he is.
- Jesus Christ, Ada!

245
00:19:17.080 --> 00:19:19.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He's gone away but he said
he'll come back.

246
00:19:19.640 --> 00:19:23.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- But they all say they'll come back.
- He's not like that.

247
00:19:23.120 --> 00:19:25.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's a good man. He promised.

248
00:19:25.120 --> 00:19:28.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[crying] He will come back, Aunt Pol,
I know he will!

249
00:19:36.240 --> 00:19:38.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Get me down a Spanish saddle, Curly.

250
00:19:38.600 --> 00:19:40.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, Tommy, a Spanish saddle.

251
00:19:40.840 --> 00:19:44.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He's a beauty.
Yeah, yeah, beautiful. Yeah.

252
00:19:50.120 --> 00:19:52.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Charlie] A fine beast
you got there, Thomas.

253
00:19:54.000 --> 00:19:57.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But is he worth falling out
with the Lee family over?

254
00:20:08.960 --> 00:20:11.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm just passing it on.

255
00:20:12.000 --> 00:20:15.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
A declaration of war.
The whole Lee clan.

256
00:20:21.080 --> 00:20:23.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The guns and now this?

257
00:20:25.400 --> 00:20:28.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The guns are not spoken of.

258
00:20:29.240 --> 00:20:30.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Right?

259
00:20:33.240 --> 00:20:34.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Tommy...

260
00:20:34.960 --> 00:20:36.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Tommy!

261
00:20:38.680 --> 00:20:42.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- You mind how you speak to me.
- Forgive me, Uncle.

262
00:20:47.520 --> 00:20:51.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's Thomas Shelby against
the whole bloody world, right?

263
00:21:15.520 --> 00:21:17.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[loud bang]

264
00:21:18.120 --> 00:21:19.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Easy...

265
00:21:21.680 --> 00:21:23.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Easy, easy...

266
00:21:25.960 --> 00:21:27.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Easy, boy.

267
00:21:27.400 --> 00:21:30.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[shushing]

268
00:21:31.680 --> 00:21:33.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
In France we used to say...

269
00:21:34.280 --> 00:21:38.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
In France we used to say,
it's just the music hall band turning up.

270
00:21:38.240 --> 00:21:40.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's just trombones
and tubas, that's all.

271
00:21:40.800 --> 00:21:42.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's just noise.

272
00:21:45.080 --> 00:21:48.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's just noise.
Hey? It's just noise.

273
00:21:49.080 --> 00:21:52.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You get used to it.
It's just noise.

274
00:21:52.480 --> 00:21:55.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Good boy. Good boy. Good boy.

275
00:22:07.600 --> 00:22:09.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Some pain there, boy?

276
00:22:14.800 --> 00:22:16.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm so sorry, Mr. Shelby.

277
00:22:19.360 --> 00:22:22.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- I'm Grace, by the way.
- I know who you are.

278
00:22:24.400 --> 00:22:27.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- What's his name?
- He doesn't have a name.

279
00:22:28.440 --> 00:22:30.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Poor boy deserves a name.

280
00:22:31.360 --> 00:22:33.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You have something
to say to me?

281
00:22:36.680 --> 00:22:39.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The other night you came into the pub
when I was singing.

282
00:22:40.560 --> 00:22:42.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You said singing wasn't allowed.

283
00:22:44.280 --> 00:22:47.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'd like there to be one night a week
when there is singing.

284
00:22:49.280 --> 00:22:51.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I think it would be good
for everyone.

285
00:22:51.600 --> 00:22:52.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Saturday nights.

286
00:22:55.000 --> 00:22:57.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Harry was too afraid
to ask you, so...

287
00:22:58.200 --> 00:22:59.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But you're not.

288
00:23:02.920 --> 00:23:04.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I am.

289
00:23:05.600 --> 00:23:07.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But I love to sing.

290
00:23:09.080 --> 00:23:12.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You sound like one of those
rich girls who come over from Dublin,

291
00:23:13.040 --> 00:23:15.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
for the races.

292
00:23:15.120 --> 00:23:16.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do you like horses?

293
00:23:18.840 --> 00:23:21.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
How do you fancy
earning some extra money?

294
00:23:21.360 --> 00:23:22.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Doing what?

295
00:23:24.960 --> 00:23:26.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Dig out a nice dress.

296
00:23:27.520 --> 00:23:29.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I want to take you to the races.

297
00:23:38.520 --> 00:23:40.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man talking indistinctly]

298
00:24:12.200 --> 00:24:13.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sorry, Mr. Shelby.

299
00:24:21.960 --> 00:24:23.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[people chattering]

300
00:24:23.360 --> 00:24:25.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Hello, Mr. Shelby,
how's it going?

301
00:24:25.440 --> 00:24:27.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Hello, Frank, how's the leg?
- Not bad.

302
00:24:27.880 --> 00:24:30.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Good. Nice to see you, son.

303
00:24:31.320 --> 00:24:32.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Morning, Charlie.

304
00:24:33.040 --> 00:24:36.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- All right, Scudboat, how are we looking?
- Looking good, Tommy.

305
00:24:36.920 --> 00:24:38.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Grand stuff.
- Tommy,

306
00:24:38.600 --> 00:24:40.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
they are all here
for Monaghan Boy.

307
00:24:40.680 --> 00:24:42.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That's what I like
to hear, Johnny boy.

308
00:24:43.040 --> 00:24:44.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And Aunt Pol wants to see you.

309
00:24:54.320 --> 00:24:56.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[inaudible]

310
00:25:37.560 --> 00:25:38.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

311
00:25:48.120 --> 00:25:50.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

312
00:25:50.080 --> 00:25:52.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Tell me the man's name, Ada.

313
00:25:53.200 --> 00:25:55.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Rudolf Valentino.

314
00:26:15.120 --> 00:26:16.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Get out!

315
00:26:16.880 --> 00:26:19.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
All of you! Go on! Now!

316
00:26:23.680 --> 00:26:25.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I said, tell me his fucking name.

317
00:26:29.640 --> 00:26:32.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Freddie fucking Thorne!

318
00:26:34.440 --> 00:26:40.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yeah. Your best mate since school.
The man who saved your life in France!

319
00:26:40.200 --> 00:26:45.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So go on! Go on, cut him!
Cut him up and chuck him in the Cut!

320
00:26:48.240 --> 00:26:53.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oye, I'm a Shelby, too, you know.
Put my fucking film back on!

321
00:27:26.440 --> 00:27:29.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So Monaghan Boy finally lost.

322
00:27:30.960 --> 00:27:32.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Third time unlucky.

323
00:27:33.520 --> 00:27:35.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We took money
from all over the city.

324
00:27:35.720 --> 00:27:38.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yeah, but you'll pay it back
to people around here.

325
00:27:39.200 --> 00:27:40.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Buy your popularity back.

326
00:27:41.240 --> 00:27:42.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Already done.

327
00:27:42.960 --> 00:27:44.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Taught you well.

328
00:27:45.520 --> 00:27:49.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And you fixed this race without
the permission of Billy Kimber?

329
00:27:50.720 --> 00:27:53.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Obviously, didn't teach you
well enough.

330
00:27:53.120 --> 00:27:55.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Rule one. You don't punch
above your weight.

331
00:27:55.760 --> 00:27:58.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Billy Kimber is there for the taking.
- Says who?

332
00:27:58.880 --> 00:28:01.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Says Tommy
and his parliament of one?

333
00:28:01.160 --> 00:28:03.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I ran this business
for five years...

334
00:28:03.680 --> 00:28:06.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yeah, while I was
away fighting, remember?

335
00:28:06.280 --> 00:28:10.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I learnt some things, such as, you strike
when your enemy is weak.

336
00:28:11.680 --> 00:28:14.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I thought you came here
to talk family business.

337
00:28:15.720 --> 00:28:17.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll deal with it.

338
00:28:17.120 --> 00:28:20.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- You're too busy taking over the world.
- Polly.

339
00:28:21.040 --> 00:28:23.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If it's about Ada,
I need to know.

340
00:28:30.680 --> 00:28:33.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ada wants you to give Freddie this letter.

341
00:28:33.960 --> 00:28:36.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
She wants Freddie to know
she's having his baby.

342
00:28:36.840 --> 00:28:39.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He deserves an opportunity
to do the right thing.

343
00:28:39.960 --> 00:28:41.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I say we give them a chance.

344
00:28:47.640 --> 00:28:50.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
For a woman who's had
a hard life with men,

345
00:28:50.400 --> 00:28:52.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
you're still full of romance, eh?

346
00:28:53.160 --> 00:28:55.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What do you think
Freddie sees in our Ada?

347
00:28:55.800 --> 00:28:57.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- That's Freddie's business.
- No.

348
00:28:57.840 --> 00:28:59.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No. I'll tell you what he sees.

349
00:28:59.840 --> 00:29:02.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He sees machine guns and rifles,

350
00:29:02.800 --> 00:29:05.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and ammunition
and some glorious revolution.

351
00:29:05.640 --> 00:29:08.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What is it you really
don't like about Freddie?

352
00:29:08.480 --> 00:29:10.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
She'll have no life
with a man on the run.

353
00:29:10.960 --> 00:29:13.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If you can't see that,
you can't see much.

354
00:29:18.200 --> 00:29:20.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Damn them for what they
did to you in France!

355
00:29:23.520 --> 00:29:26.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Tell Ada, Freddie went to America.

356
00:29:27.240 --> 00:29:28.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Or Russia.

357
00:29:28.680 --> 00:29:32.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Polly, it would do no good for Ada
to bring a baby into the world alone.

358
00:29:32.960 --> 00:29:34.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Pol, listen.

359
00:29:34.320 --> 00:29:37.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The truth is you would have
hit me with that thing,

360
00:29:37.440 --> 00:29:40.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
if it weren't for the fact
that you know I'm right!

361
00:29:44.960 --> 00:29:46.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I thought I heard
someone knocking.

362
00:29:47.840 --> 00:29:49.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Couldn't get back to sleep.

363
00:29:53.120 --> 00:29:57.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Polly] The longer you leave it,
the worse it gets.

364
00:30:04.760 --> 00:30:08.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Believe me, I know.

365
00:30:10.720 --> 00:30:12.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I was 16.

366
00:30:14.760 --> 00:30:16.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And I didn't dare tell anyone.

367
00:30:17.640 --> 00:30:19.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Polly, Freddie will come back.

368
00:30:20.200 --> 00:30:22.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
In the end I did it myself.

369
00:30:24.280 --> 00:30:26.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I did it to myself.

370
00:30:26.800 --> 00:30:28.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And I almost died.

371
00:30:29.520 --> 00:30:31.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And he didn't come back.

372
00:30:31.840 --> 00:30:34.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They don't.
Why should they?

373
00:30:34.880 --> 00:30:36.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You know the words.

374
00:30:36.560 --> 00:30:39.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
"You're a whore,
the baby's a bastard."

375
00:30:39.680 --> 00:30:42.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But there's no word for the man
who doesn't come back.

376
00:30:46.240 --> 00:30:50.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
One day, on your wedding day,

377
00:30:50.640 --> 00:30:53.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
you'll have a good man on your arm,

378
00:30:54.000 --> 00:30:59.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and you will say,
"Polly, thank you for common sense."

379
00:31:08.040 --> 00:31:09.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This woman is in Cardiff.

380
00:31:11.240 --> 00:31:13.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We'll take the train tomorrow.

381
00:31:16.600 --> 00:31:19.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Go to the castle
afterwards for a treat.

382
00:32:12.800 --> 00:32:17.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I chose this place because it is outside
both of our jurisdictions.

383
00:32:19.800 --> 00:32:21.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do you want tea?

384
00:32:23.040 --> 00:32:25.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Inspector, I responded
to your invitation,

385
00:32:25.560 --> 00:32:28.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
because I want us to
understand each other.

386
00:32:29.000 --> 00:32:30.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I am a businessman.

387
00:32:31.520 --> 00:32:33.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I want to make
my business successful.

388
00:32:34.760 --> 00:32:37.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And I want my city run peacefully.

389
00:32:38.240 --> 00:32:41.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If the city is peaceful,
business can thrive.

390
00:32:42.880 --> 00:32:45.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So we are on the same side?

391
00:32:46.440 --> 00:32:48.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I think perhaps we could be.

392
00:32:55.040 --> 00:32:56.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now...

393
00:33:00.160 --> 00:33:04.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
How can we be on the same side
when I see things like this?

394
00:33:06.240 --> 00:33:12.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My men found this
in the bedroom of a known communist.

395
00:33:13.560 --> 00:33:15.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It has your sister's name on it.

396
00:33:17.680 --> 00:33:20.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It was obvious she had been
sleeping in his bed.

397
00:33:21.760 --> 00:33:26.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Are you also in bed
with the communists, Mr. Shelby?

398
00:33:27.080 --> 00:33:29.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I do not share their fantasy.

399
00:33:29.960 --> 00:33:31.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And as for my sister,

400
00:33:31.720 --> 00:33:34.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I have already dealt
with the situation.

401
00:33:34.880 --> 00:33:37.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Freddie Thorne is
at the very top of my list.

402
00:33:37.560 --> 00:33:39.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Cross him off.

403
00:33:39.560 --> 00:33:41.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He won't be returning to the city.

404
00:33:43.200 --> 00:33:45.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I will make him part of our deal.

405
00:33:47.000 --> 00:33:48.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What deal?

406
00:33:52.800 --> 00:33:56.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You and your Specials will leave
my businesses alone from now on.

407
00:33:56.960 --> 00:34:00.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No more raids into our territory,
no more smashing up pubs,

408
00:34:00.600 --> 00:34:02.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
no more lifting my runners.

409
00:34:02.400 --> 00:34:05.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You turn a blind eye to
all of my gambling operations.

410
00:34:05.600 --> 00:34:06.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Also...

411
00:34:07.440 --> 00:34:11.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I am planning an expansion
onto the race tracks.

412
00:34:11.280 --> 00:34:14.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I intend to do business
with Billy Kimber.

413
00:34:14.520 --> 00:34:18.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He runs most of the legal
track side betting outside of London.

414
00:34:18.440 --> 00:34:20.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He has policemen on his payroll.

415
00:34:20.720 --> 00:34:24.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I want you to put in a word with
the Chief Inspector at Gloucestershire,

416
00:34:25.000 --> 00:34:28.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that his men should leave me alone
when I make my move.

417
00:34:31.840 --> 00:34:34.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Forgive me.
I don't seem to have a pen

418
00:34:34.280 --> 00:34:37.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to write down this rather
long list of demands.

419
00:34:40.920 --> 00:34:42.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And what do I get in return?

420
00:34:44.560 --> 00:34:46.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have what you're looking for.

421
00:34:52.040 --> 00:34:53.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have the guns.

422
00:34:56.000 --> 00:34:57.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What guns?

423
00:34:57.440 --> 00:35:00.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- I'm not here to play games--
- Wait, wait.

424
00:35:11.440 --> 00:35:16.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Twenty-five Lewis machine guns.
50 carbines, 10,000 rounds of ammunition.

425
00:35:16.760 --> 00:35:22.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
All in a crate bound for Libya,
stolen from the BSA factory proofing bay.

426
00:35:23.080 --> 00:35:26.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm guessing they sent you to Birmingham
to get those guns back.

427
00:35:26.880 --> 00:35:29.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, it's me that has them.

428
00:35:31.800 --> 00:35:36.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I have left word with men I trust that
if I am taken into police custody

429
00:35:36.080 --> 00:35:37.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
for whatever reason,

430
00:35:37.440 --> 00:35:39.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
those guns will be shipped to Liverpool.

431
00:35:39.960 --> 00:35:42.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
From there they will be sent directly
to Belfast,

432
00:35:42.920 --> 00:35:45.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and sold to the Irish Republican Army.

433
00:35:46.560 --> 00:35:49.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
All your good work in Ireland
would be undone.

434
00:35:49.360 --> 00:35:51.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Each stolen weapon
is numbered and marked.

435
00:35:52.000 --> 00:35:56.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If I sell them to the IRA, it won't
be long before Mr. Churchill finds out.

436
00:35:56.560 --> 00:36:01.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I imagine you got into enough trouble over
the burning of the King's photographs.

437
00:36:01.400 --> 00:36:03.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That was just a taster.

438
00:36:03.320 --> 00:36:09.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If those guns reach Belfast,
your life in the force is over.

439
00:36:10.080 --> 00:36:13.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
When I have achieved
what I have set out to achieve,

440
00:36:13.160 --> 00:36:15.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I will let you know
where to find the guns.

441
00:36:15.840 --> 00:36:19.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You'll be a hero,
you will probably get a medal.

442
00:36:22.000 --> 00:36:23.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm a fair man.

443
00:36:24.320 --> 00:36:25.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's a fair offer.

444
00:36:28.000 --> 00:36:29.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do we have a deal?

445
00:36:38.160 --> 00:36:39.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I need an answer.

446
00:36:40.160 --> 00:36:41.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Right now.

447
00:36:46.240 --> 00:36:47.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Very well.

448
00:36:49.800 --> 00:36:53.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But I would prefer
if we don't shake hands on it.

449
00:37:06.640 --> 00:37:09.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Now why would I
shake the hand of a man,

450
00:37:09.360 --> 00:37:11.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
who didn't even fight
for his country?

451
00:37:22.120 --> 00:37:25.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[opera music playing]

452
00:37:26.680 --> 00:37:30.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[singing in foreign language]

453
00:37:51.120 --> 00:37:52.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[knock at door]

454
00:37:55.560 --> 00:37:56.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Grace.

455
00:38:02.880 --> 00:38:05.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have new information.

456
00:38:08.480 --> 00:38:11.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Thomas Shelby</i>
<i>is now the beginning,</i>

457
00:38:11.240 --> 00:38:14.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
the middle and end of your mission.

458
00:38:26.200 --> 00:38:27.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So what shall I do?

459
00:38:29.360 --> 00:38:31.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It hurts me as much as it,

460
00:38:31.720 --> 00:38:35.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
as it would a father sending his
own daughter into a whore house,

461
00:38:38.520 --> 00:38:41.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but no matter how repugnant it may be,

462
00:38:42.280 --> 00:38:46.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
you must do everything you can
to get close to him,

463
00:38:47.320 --> 00:38:51.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and find out where those guns are hidden.

464
00:38:54.440 --> 00:38:57.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Of course, when I say,
"Everything," I don't mean...

465
00:38:59.200 --> 00:39:02.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You underestimate me in every way.

466
00:39:11.600 --> 00:39:12.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Here...

467
00:39:23.400 --> 00:39:28.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You are now active in a military operation
on behalf of the Crown.

468
00:39:30.160 --> 00:39:34.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And I wish to God,
circumstance hadn't chosen you.

469
00:39:35.880 --> 00:39:37.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's what I am trained for.

470
00:39:38.800 --> 00:39:40.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm late for my shift.

471
00:39:44.840 --> 00:39:45.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Grace...

472
00:39:47.840 --> 00:39:49.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My heart is with you.

473
00:39:58.400 --> 00:40:00.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[dramatic opera music playing]

474
00:40:02.560 --> 00:40:05.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[singing in foreign language]

475
00:40:06.000 --> 00:40:07.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[screaming]

476
00:40:10.080 --> 00:40:11.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gunshot]

477
00:40:25.000 --> 00:40:26.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[panting]

478
00:40:48.720 --> 00:40:51.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Tom! Tom!

479
00:40:51.360 --> 00:40:54.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Tom, you better come quick, Tom!
Come! Come!

480
00:41:22.640 --> 00:41:25.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Curly, tell me.
- It's a curse, Tom.

481
00:41:27.600 --> 00:41:31.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Curly. Curly. Curly. Shh. Curly. Curly.

482
00:41:32.520 --> 00:41:35.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Tell me. Tell me, Curly,
what's wrong with the horse?

483
00:41:36.000 --> 00:41:38.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You bought it at the fair in bad feeling.

484
00:41:38.600 --> 00:41:42.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The Lees put a bad seed in the hoof.
Got an old woman to put a spell!

485
00:41:42.760 --> 00:41:44.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[mumbling]

486
00:41:47.560 --> 00:41:49.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So those Lee bastards cursed her.

487
00:41:51.160 --> 00:41:54.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Whatever it is, he says
it spread to the other foot.

488
00:41:54.640 --> 00:41:57.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's going to his heart
by tomorrow, I'd say.

489
00:41:57.680 --> 00:42:01.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Seen curses like this twice.
Can't take them back, Tom!

490
00:42:01.200 --> 00:42:02.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No! No!

491
00:42:03.000 --> 00:42:05.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I told you, Tommy.

492
00:42:05.440 --> 00:42:08.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Better enemies to have
than black blood Gypsies.

493
00:42:12.080 --> 00:42:13.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Get out.

494
00:42:14.600 --> 00:42:16.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Get out, Curly.

495
00:42:22.240 --> 00:42:23.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm sorry.

496
00:42:35.080 --> 00:42:36.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gunshot]

497
00:42:52.840 --> 00:42:54.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[banging on door]

498
00:43:02.600 --> 00:43:06.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- We're closed, Mr. Shelby.
- Just get me a drink.

499
00:43:13.880 --> 00:43:15.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[coughs]

500
00:43:20.040 --> 00:43:21.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Shall I leave you alone?

501
00:43:23.280 --> 00:43:25.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I came here for company.

502
00:43:26.160 --> 00:43:29.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Where's Harry?
- He took the night off.

503
00:43:32.040 --> 00:43:33.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And went to the pictures.

504
00:43:40.960 --> 00:43:42.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How's your beautiful horse?

505
00:43:52.480 --> 00:43:54.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I just put a bullet in his head.

506
00:43:58.680 --> 00:44:00.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Was he lame?

507
00:44:03.120 --> 00:44:05.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He looked at me the wrong way.

508
00:44:06.600 --> 00:44:10.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's not a good idea to look
at Tommy Shelby the wrong way.

509
00:44:15.240 --> 00:44:19.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- What a waste.
- Yeah. A waste is what it is.

510
00:44:26.080 --> 00:44:27.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You know, in France...

511
00:44:32.160 --> 00:44:35.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
In France, I got used to seeing men die.

512
00:44:36.720 --> 00:44:39.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Never got used to seeing horses die.

513
00:44:41.080 --> 00:44:42.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They die badly.

514
00:44:49.600 --> 00:44:51.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I dug out a dress like you asked.

515
00:44:52.920 --> 00:44:54.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thanks.

516
00:44:56.480 --> 00:44:58.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Is it Cheltenham
you're talking about?

517
00:45:05.960 --> 00:45:08.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Cheltenham's a grand affair, is it not?

518
00:45:08.360 --> 00:45:10.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The King will be there.

519
00:45:10.120 --> 00:45:12.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- King George?
- No.

520
00:45:13.600 --> 00:45:17.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
King Billy Kimber and all his men.

521
00:45:19.480 --> 00:45:21.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And what must I do?

522
00:45:21.240 --> 00:45:24.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
For two pounds you will do
what I ask you to do.

523
00:45:25.680 --> 00:45:27.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I want three.

524
00:45:28.760 --> 00:45:32.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If I'm meeting a king,
I won't be wearing a cheap dress.

525
00:45:35.440 --> 00:45:39.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And I asked you to let me sing.
That's part of the deal now too.

526
00:45:40.600 --> 00:45:42.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Since when?

527
00:45:44.080 --> 00:45:45.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Since you nearly smiled.

528
00:45:50.360 --> 00:45:52.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Saturday nights.
Open and easy.

529
00:45:52.920 --> 00:45:56.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Everyone gets to sing their song,
just like we did in Dublin.

530
00:45:56.600 --> 00:46:00.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You never worked in Dublin,
so don't lie to me.

531
00:46:00.320 --> 00:46:04.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I asked around about that pub
you said you used to work in.

532
00:46:04.240 --> 00:46:05.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have friends over there.

533
00:46:06.840 --> 00:46:08.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No one has heard of you.

534
00:46:15.040 --> 00:46:16.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My guess is,

535
00:46:17.520 --> 00:46:21.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
you are a girl from a good family,
who got herself pregnant.

536
00:46:24.960 --> 00:46:26.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's not something I want known.

537
00:46:27.040 --> 00:46:30.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And bringing a child into the world alone
ruined your life.

538
00:46:31.480 --> 00:46:32.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Right?

539
00:46:36.680 --> 00:46:40.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So I'm right and Polly is wrong.

540
00:46:41.520 --> 00:46:43.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Right about what?

541
00:46:43.880 --> 00:46:45.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It doesn't matter.

542
00:46:46.800 --> 00:46:48.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It looks like it matters to you.

543
00:46:49.400 --> 00:46:51.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Family business.

544
00:46:54.920 --> 00:46:56.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You won't tell anyone my secret.

545
00:46:58.040 --> 00:47:00.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do you think I tell people things?

546
00:47:04.320 --> 00:47:05.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So what do you sing?

547
00:47:07.760 --> 00:47:10.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Anything you want.
- Right.

548
00:47:11.000 --> 00:47:12.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Get up on a chair.

549
00:47:13.360 --> 00:47:14.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Okay.

550
00:47:21.920 --> 00:47:23.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Happy or sad?

551
00:47:27.000 --> 00:47:28.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sad.

552
00:47:29.720 --> 00:47:30.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Okay.

553
00:47:31.040 --> 00:47:34.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But I warn you,
it will break your heart.

554
00:47:35.560 --> 00:47:37.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Already broken.

555
00:47:41.960 --> 00:47:47.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>♪ In a neat little town </i>
<i>They call Belfast ♪</i>

556
00:47:47.800 --> 00:47:51.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>♪ Apprentice to trade</i>
<i>I was bound ♪</i>

557
00:47:52.520 --> 00:47:58.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ Many an hour sweet happiness ♪</i>

558
00:47:58.440 --> 00:48:03.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ Had I spent in that neat little town ♪</i>

559
00:48:04.480 --> 00:48:09.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ A sad misfortune came over me ♪</i>

560
00:48:10.040 --> 00:48:14.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ Which caused me to stray from the land ♪</i>

561
00:48:16.080 --> 00:48:23.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ Far away from my friends and relations ♪</i>

562
00:48:24.840 --> 00:48:31.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ Betrayed by the black velvet band ♪</i>

563
00:48:32.080 --> 00:48:36.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ Her eyes, they shone like diamonds ♪</i>

564
00:48:37.160 --> 00:48:41.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ I thought her the queen of the land ♪</i>

565
00:48:42.800 --> 00:48:48.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>♪ And her hair</i>
